    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:44f82abb-bdd4-4229-a2a0-6e1ab3b73a4a",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-description</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is an energetic 8-year-old boy from Brno, Czech Republic, who normally attends second grade at a local primary school. He is of average build for his age, with tousled brown hair and an usually rosy complexion — today, however, he looks pale and tired, with sunken eyes and dry lips that hint at mild dehydration. He arrived at the paediatric outpatient clinic holding his mother's hand, occasionally clutching his abdomen and grimacing with cramp-like pain.\n\nOver the past two days, {patientName} has been experiencing frequent loose to watery stools — up to six episodes per day — accompanied by low-grade fever and mild nausea [SNOMED:A09.0]. His mother reports that the diarrhoea started abruptly the morning after a birthday party where several children ate food that had been left out for hours. Two classmates from the same party are reportedly unwell with similar symptoms.\n\nOutside of this illness, {patientName} is an active child who loves football (he plays on a local youth team), cycling with his father, and building LEGO models in the evenings. He lives with both parents and a younger sister in a flat in central Brno. His diet is otherwise balanced; he drinks adequate fluids and eats a variety of fruits and vegetables.\n\nHis mother is worried because he refused breakfast today and has been lying on the sofa all morning, which is very unlike him. She brought a stool sample as requested by the telephone triage nurse. {patientName} is cooperative during the examination, though fatigued, and is able to communicate his symptoms clearly."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:4e8f6941-250a-48e0-b905-3db3d8f3a445",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant chronic medical conditions and has not been hospitalised previously. His vaccinations are up to date according to the Czech national immunisation schedule, including rotavirus vaccine administered in infancy. He had a mild upper respiratory tract infection six months ago that resolved without treatment.\n\n{patientName} has no known food allergies, though his mother notes he tends to have a sensitive stomach with loose stools whenever he eats too much fatty food. There is no history of recurrent diarrhoea, blood in stool, or weight loss to suggest an underlying inflammatory or malabsorptive condition. Family history is notable for irritable bowel syndrome in his mother and type 2 diabetes in his paternal grandfather.\n\nLifestyle factors: {patientName} is physically active, eats a home-cooked diet most days, and attends a school canteen for lunch. The suspected source of the current illness is contaminated food at a birthday party two days prior to presentation. No recent travel outside the Czech Republic is reported."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
